(139, 1, '2014-01-15 19:42:47', '2014-01-15 19:42:47', 'LOS ANGELES - December 12, 2013 - <a href="http://oakwood.com/" target="_blank">Oakwood Worldwide</a>, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartments, has entered into a 5-year management agreement with Ascendas Hospitality Trust ("A-HTRUST") beginning January 1, 2014, adding yet another property to the company''s already strong presence in Tokyo, Japan. The fund managers of A-HTRUST are part of the Ascendas Group, Asia''s leading provider of business space solutions. This venture supports Oakwood Worldwide''s strategy for continued growth in both established and emerging global markets.\n\nThe addition of the Oakwood Apartments Ariake, Tokyo, formerly B:CONTE Ariake, gives Oakwood Worldwide more than 580 apartments within eight Tokyo properties. The property offers easy access from Tokyo Haneda Airport and is located near the Tokyo Waterfront Secondary City, Palette Town, Tokyo Big Sight, Tokyo Disneyland and the Ariake Colosseum - home to a number of 2020 Olympic events.\n\n"The business traveler is going to love our apartments in Ariake," said Mr PG Mathew, managing director for Oakwood Worldwide''s portfolio of 27 properties in the Asia Pacific region. "The product is extraordinary and ideally located near major businesses and the Olympic Park. Moreover, we are in negotiations to offer this as our first serviced apartment in Japan located within a zone that permits stays of less than 30 days."\n\nWith 122 apartments, the property has a mix of 98 studio and 24 one-bedroom apartments that offer panoramic city and bay views. The apartments come with a fully equipped modern kitchenette, in-unit washer and dryer and free Wi-Fi. Residents will also benefit from the concierge service, fitness center and access to the adjacent hotel''s restaurant and café .\n\n"We are very pleased to have our property carry the Oakwood name," said Mr Tan Juay Hiang, chief executive officer of the fund managers of A-HTRUST. "With Oakwood''s strong branding and established track record, we are confident they will enhance the services and performance of our asset in Tokyo. We look forward to a successful partnership with Oakwood Worldwide."\n\nOakwood Worldwide currently maintains seven other branded properties in Japan located in Akasaka, Aoyama, Azabujyuban, Roppongi, Shirokane and Tokyo Midtown. A ninth property, the Oakwood Residence Tokyo is scheduled to open in the spring of 2015.', 'Oakwood Worldwide® Signs Management Agreement for Eighth Tokyo Property', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '117-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-01-15 19:42:47', '2014-01-15 19:42:47', '', 117, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/2014/01/117-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(140, 1, '2014-01-15 19:45:16', '2014-01-15 19:45:16', 'LOS ANGELES - February 4, 2013 - Oakwood Worldwide, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartment solutions, has expanded its Canadian operations with the opening of a Toronto-based office and the hiring of 20-year corporate housing veteran, Elle Crane, to support the company''s corporate housing partners and continue to strengthen Oakwood Worldwide''s footprint in Canada.\r\n\r\nOakwood has maintained a presence in Canada for the past 10 years, providing furnished, temporary housing across the country. The opening of the Canada office represents the company''s commitment to a significant increase in demand for housing across Canada. Many cities throughout the Alberta province are attracting businesses who want to explore the region''s untapped natural resources. Companies involved in the industries of oil, gas, energy, mining and potash have begun sending employees and contractors to the area in greater numbers over the past two years.\r\n\r\n"Canada is experiencing a surge that is showing no signs of slowing down," said Maria Schmitt, general manager for the Americas region at Oakwood Worldwide. "Having our office in Toronto and a well-connected, experienced supply chain manager like Elle on board is giving us an incredible advantage for meeting the unique demands of our clients in the region."\r\n\r\nThe company''s response to mounting business in Canada is one of several key indicators that support Oakwood Worldwide''s continued focus on global growth. In 2012, the company acquired the ExecuStay corporate housing brand from Marriott International, expanding its presence in the United States. Further, Oakwood Worldwide recently announced a global realignment that allows for a strategic on-the-ground presence to service clients in the Europe, Middle East and Africa regions, along with those in the Asia Pacific regions.\r\n\r\nThe Oakwood Worldwide Canada office is located at 2 Bloor Street West in Toronto, Ontario. Elle Crane may be reached at +416-972-1432.', 'Oakwood Worldwide&reg; Expands Global Operations with Opening of Canada Office', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-worldwide-expands-global-operations-with-opening-of-canada-office', '', '', '2014-01-15 19:48:44', '2014-01-15 19:48:44', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press-releases&#038;p=140', 0, 'press-releases', '', 0),
(141, 1, '2014-01-13 19:55:36', '2014-01-13 19:55:36', 'LOS ANGELES - April 24, 2013 - Oakwood Worldwide, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartments, has expanded its Worldwide Sales &amp; Service Center, located in Phoenix, Ariz., to accommodate a 50 percent increase in staff with the goal of providing greater operational efficiency as part of the company''s continued focus on global growth.\r\n\r\nThe centralized facility, one of three Oakwood Worldwide has throughout the world, provides customers of both Oakwood and ExecuStay brands with more efficient processing as well as a 24-hour customer care center, which is a new feature for ExecuStay customers. The company''s similar centers operate out of London and Singapore.\r\n\r\nThe staff of the WSSC has increased rapidly through a combination of centralized services, new initiatives and the recent acquisition of the ExecuStay brand. Oakwood Worldwide has signed a lease for additional office space within their current facility as the company is seeing continued growth in 2013. Phoenix, which is home to customer care centers for more than 200 companies, offers a rich talent base for Oakwood Worldwide.\r\n\r\nThe WSSC is core to Oakwood Worldwide''s service delivery model, providing 24/7/365 sales and customer service, as well as, international reservations, hotel reservations and centralized accounts receivable and payable teams. With the addition of ExecuStay operations, the WSSC will employ more than 230 residents in the Phoenix area.\r\n\r\n"The WSSC in Phoenix is Oakwood''s Center of Excellence where we develop innovative technologies to streamline our processes and provide the best possible customer service experience," said Scott McDonald, vice president, Call Center Operations at Oakwood Worldwide. "We are always looking for ways we can improve, and through the integration of ExecuStay operations, our award-winning customer service will be even better."\r\n\r\nPhoenix was named one of the "Best Places for Business and Careers" by Forbes magazine in 2012. Forbes also recently named Phoenix a "Top 10 Potential Boom City" and a "Top 15 City for Working Moms." According to a 2012 Metro Monitor report from the Brookings Institute, Phoenix has the third strongest economy in the nation compared to 100 of the largest metro areas in the country.\r\n\r\nThe Oakwood Worldwide Sales &amp; Service Center is located at 9630 N. 25th Avenue, Suite 300 Phoenix, AZ 85021. Those interested in career opportunities should visit <a href="http://oakwoodcareers.com"> www.oakwoodcareers.com.</a>', 'Oakwood Worldwide<sup>&reg;</sup> Expands Operations at Sales & Service Center', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-worldwide-expands-operations-at-sales-service-center', '', '', '2014-01-31 18:21:24', '2014-01-31 18:21:24', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=141', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
