(184, 1, '2012-03-05 21:18:43', '2012-03-05 21:18:43', 'LOS ANGELES, March 5, 2012 - Oakwood, the global leader in furnished and serviced corporate apartments and residences, climbed to No. 39 in Training Magazine''s 12th Annual list of the Top 125 companies for outstanding employee training and development programs. This is the seventh consecutive year Oakwood was recognized and the company now ranks as the top provider among other recognized hospitality industry brands. Oakwood''s ranking has been rising and shot up 60 spots from No. 99 in 2011 to No. 39 this year.\r\n\r\nOakwood was recognized for its overall commitment to learning and development for its more than 2,500 associates worldwide. The company''s world-class training and development programs are supported by Oakwood University, which features comprehensive classroom and online courses. Oakwood continually updates its offerings with innovative training and development programs, including a new Career Planning Program which includes an Associate Guide, competencies and training plans matched to associate needs.\r\n\r\n"We''ve made a significant investment in transforming our culture into a best-in-class service organization and an employer of choice," says Ana Castellanos, Oakwood''s vice president of Human Resources. "We''re deeply committed to giving our associates and leaders all the tools and skills they need to grow and thrive in their careers while providing our customers with top-notch service."\r\n\r\nThe nation''s Fortune 500 companies consider Training''s Top 125 list as prestigious. To be considered, companies must participate in an extensive, multi-phase application process and submit both quantitative and qualitative data. The judges consider many criteria, including staffing levels, training budgets, new workforce development programs, best practices, and talent management before they ultimately decide on the Top 125.\r\n\r\nThis year''s winners were announced on February 13 at a ceremony in Atlanta. Oakwood joined many highly regarded national and international companies on the list, including Verizon, UPS, Farmers Insurance, MasterCard, MetLife, and Miami Children''s Hospital.\r\n\r\nAbout Oakwood\r\nOakwood is the global leader and provider of furnished and serviced apartments. For one need or many, local or around the globe - Oakwood offers flexible, easy-to-use, custom solutions to meet any temporary housing need.\r\n\r\nA wide range of inventory and supplier management options allows Oakwood to provide the optimal housing solution whenever and wherever needed. With more than 2,500 Oakwood associates worldwide, over 25,000 apartments, and more than 400 network partners, Oakwood delivers the service and reliability clients can trust.\r\n\r\nIts staff of trained professionals throughout the world, innovative technologies, and unparalleled customer service have made Oakwood the premier choice in temporary housing solutions for 50 years.', 'Oakwood Ranks in Training Magazine''s Top 125 For Seventh Year in a Row', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-ranks-in-training-magazines-top-125-for-seventh-year-in-a-row', '', '', '2014-01-30 22:38:34', '2014-01-30 22:38:34', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=184', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
(185, 1, '2014-01-20 21:34:44', '2014-01-20 21:34:44', 'LOS ANGELES - January 16, 2014 - Oakwood Worldwide, the global leader in corporate housing and serviced apartments, announces the addition of Daniel Mohanrao as director of sales for the company''s western region. In this capacity, Mohanrao will be responsible for leading a sales team to deliver against strategy for location-based clients.\r\n\r\nMohanrao will manage strategic growth for business in the western states. His focus will be on ensuring customers'' objectives are met and the right resources are in place to service those accounts.\r\n\r\n"Daniel is a strong addition to our sales leadership team with his extensive global background in sales and business development," said T.J. Spencer, vice president of sales at Oakwood Worldwide. "Under his leadership we expect to grow preference and market share in the western region by delivering to our clients the right housing solutions for their business needs."\r\n\r\nMohanrao brings to Oakwood Worldwide 15 years of experience in sales management and business development. Most recently, he served as country manager for FedEx Office Canada, where he was responsible for overall company strategy and direction, including sales, marketing, operations and training. In his 10-year tenure with FedEx Office, he held a number of positions of increasing responsibility, including head of sales for the company''s international division, where he defined strategy for the commercial sales teams in Japan, Korea, China and Canada. Mohanrao received the highest honor from FedEx, the Five Star award, which recognizes team members who have enhanced service and profitability and exemplified the spirit of teamwork.\r\n\r\nMohanrao holds a bachelor''s degree from San Francisco State University. He will operate out of Oakwood Worldwide''s office in San Francisco.', 'Oakwood Worldwide<sup>&reg;</sup>Adds Seasoned, Global Leader to Sales Team', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'oakwood-worldwide-adds-seasoned-global-leader-to-sales-team', '', '', '2014-01-31 18:20:01', '2014-01-31 18:20:01', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=press_releases&#038;p=185', 0, 'press_releases', '', 0),
(186, 1, '2013-11-20 21:48:08', '2013-11-20 21:48:08', 'The Forum for Expatriate Management (FEM) has recognized Oakwood Worldwide with the European Expatriate Management and Mobility Award (EMMA) for Corporate Housing Provider of the Year. The company was selected for its comprehensive and customized approach to meeting its customers'' corporate housing needs.', 'Corporate Housing Provider of the Year', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'corporate-housing-provider-of-the-year', '', '', '2014-01-21 20:37:59', '2014-01-21 20:37:59', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/2014/?post_type=awards&#038;p=186', 0, 'awards', '', 0),
